snippet.textDisplay:
"Does the average person in 2020 "need" a laptop/computer or is a smartphone enough?"


I think the question should be: "Can you really do any serious work and production on a little itty bitty screen?" Even many 'average people'' wind up needing to do real work on a computer on occasion. Bottom line is, yea, you can do a whole lot of stuff on a cell phone but that doesn't mean it's the best or most efficient way of doing so.


A cell phone is great for consumption but not for any 'real' work or gaming. Also, older people will tell you that aging eyes don't like smaller screens either.


Bottom line: If you are not doing a lot of work and/or happy with the types of games that work well on smaller screens,.. cell phones great. REAL work and production? well.. you all already know the answer to that.
